{
  "texts": [
    "We had IRB (Institutional Review Board) permission to analyze students' anonymous code.",
    "We filtered the write-code problems by topic, difficulty level, diversity of correct and incorrect code clusters, and common error types in the buggy submissions.",
    "After filtering, we selected 10 programming problems that covered various programming topics with different difficulty levels, solution strategies, and common error types.",
    "We randomly sampled 50 incorrect code submissions from each of the 10 problems, leading to 500 incorrect code inputs.To account for variation at the student level, each sampled code submission came from a unique student.",
    "Based on these 500 inputs, we obtained 500 personalized solutions Stage 1 (Section 4.1) and puzzles from Stage 2 (Section 4.2) for evaluation."
  ]
}